+## 2026-04-01 Processing: exploration-001-packet-sign-canonicity-gate-report.md + meta-exploration-001.md
+
+### Findings extracted (factual — exploration-001-packet-sign-canonicity-gate-report.md):
+
+This exploration tested whether the new `SD_part` / `SD_target` sign split canonizes the old packetized Tao-circuit backup. It concluded no: the sign language is sharper, but the object still moves under harmless bookkeeping and refinement changes.
+
+- Splitting the packet sign defect into `SD_part` and `SD_target` does not produce a canonical exact-NS packet/sign object: `SD_part` fails conjugate-pair representative invariance and packet-refinement invariance, while `SD_target` and `Leak` still depend on desired-triad witness bookkeeping -> filed at `factual/navier-stokes/exact-ns-helical-sign-canonicity-failure.md` (NEW)
+- The older packet non-canonicity entry is now sharpened with the failed sign-functionals repair: even refined sign bookkeeping does not freeze the packet family into one theorem-facing object -> incorporated into `factual/navier-stokes/packetized-tao-circuit-noncanonical.md` (UPDATE)
+
+### Findings extracted (meta — meta-exploration-001.md):
+
+- Before authorizing Phase 1 computations on a refined observable, require it to survive harmless representative and refinement changes; otherwise the mission is still at the canonization gate -> filed at `meta/goal-design/require-harmless-change-invariance-for-observables.md` (NEW)
+- If a follow-on mission only adds new observables to the same non-canonical object family, predecessor negatives may already settle it -> incorporated into `meta/goal-design/check-faithful-support-shrinkage-before-narrowing.md` (UPDATE)
+- Explorer skeleton-buffering stall without synthesis -> SKIPPED as duplicate operational lesson (covered by `meta/system-behavior/explorer-stalling-and-nudge-pattern.md`)
+
+### Cross-references:
+
+- exact-ns-helical-sign-canonicity-failure.md -> packetized-tao-circuit-noncanonical.md (specific failed repair sits inside the broader packet negative)
+- require-harmless-change-invariance-for-observables.md -> check-faithful-support-shrinkage-before-narrowing.md (first compare to predecessor object, then test whether the new observable is canonical on it)
