# Meta Library — INDEX

Operational lessons about how the Atlas system works, learned from the quantum-gravity-2, riemann-hypothesis, yang-mills, yang-mills-conjecture, yang-mills-validation, navier-stokes, compton-unruh, classicality-budget, stochastic-electrodynamics, amplituhedron, thermal-time, barandes-stochastic, and vasseur-pressure missions. (**exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck meta-001**: NEW `require-harmless-change-invariance-for-observables` (goal-design — before Phase 1 computations, require new observables to survive representative relabeling and harmless refinements); UPDATED `check-faithful-support-shrinkage-before-narrowing` (goal-design — adding new observables to the same non-canonical object family does not reopen Phase 1). Prior: **exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall meta-003**: UPDATED `fix-observability-conventions-before-precursor-search` (goal-design — after freezing the selected pair, first ask whether the exact identity has any backward-memory term linking the earlier slab to the later event; if not, stop rather than renaming the same defect). Prior: **exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall meta-002**: UPDATED `fix-observability-conventions-before-precursor-search` (goal-design — once Phase 0 fixes the event cylinder, use the literal earlier slab as the precursor region; once one pair survives, freeze it and attack one theorem target rather than reopening candidate selection). Prior: **exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall meta-001**: NEW `fix-observability-conventions-before-precursor-search` (goal-design — once a Phase 0 event is defined by a fixed interface and witness channel, freeze those conventions and vary only one precursor observable); UPDATED `definition-extraction-gates-computation` (methodology — if exact-PDE post-processing plus observability conventions already defines the object, do not force a reduced model). Prior: **exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall meta-001**: NEW `check-faithful-support-shrinkage-before-narrowing` (goal-design — before launching a narrowed mechanism mission, test whether the narrowed feature actually reduces the faithful exact support; if not, predecessor negatives may already transfer); UPDATED `require-mechanism-layer-maps` (goal-design — causal roles like trigger/clock/conduit are not standalone theorem objects; state the surrounding chain that makes them meaningful). Prior: **exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit meta-001**: NEW `coefficient-weighted-amplitude-level-leakage` (methodology — monomial-level mechanisms need coefficient-weighted amplitude-level leakage, not triad counts or packet energies); NEW `build-adversarial-suppression-into-first-audit` (goal-design — the first leakage audit should include a configuration chosen to suppress the alleged obstruction); UPDATED `require-mechanism-layer-maps` (goal-design — if the reduced mechanism is quadratic, encode it as a monomial hypergraph, not just a node graph); UPDATED `definition-extraction-gates-computation` (methodology — one exact law from primary sources can be the missing layer that closes a definition gate). Prior: **anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall meta-002**: NEW `toy-subsystem-isolation-inside-exact-network` (methodology — in toy-mechanism vs exact-PDE comparisons, test whether the reduced subsystem survives the full exact interaction graph); UPDATED `require-mechanism-layer-maps` (goal-design — add literal channel/intervention tables for firewall work); UPDATED `preload-context-from-prior-work` (goal-design — preload closure stacks, not just positive findings, when dead routes are already known). Prior: **anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall meta-001**: NEW `require-mechanism-layer-maps`; UPDATED `definition-extraction-gates-computation`. Earlier: **far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole meta**: NEW `reconcile-notation-before-falsification` (methodology — when a surviving lead is inherited across different decompositions/vocabularies, reconcile notation before falsification; prevents testing harmonic `P_{k1}` when the actual bottleneck is local `P_{k21}`). Earlier: **vasseur-pressure S2-E008 meta**: NEW `allow-analytic-extremizer-over-computation` (goal-design — when designing optimization-based explorations, allow explorers to find analytic extremizers instead of over-specifying SDP/LP approach; constant field extremizer made entire SDP unnecessary). Earlier: S2-E007 meta — adversarial-review-needs-complete-parallel-context, adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure update; S2-E006 meta — tool-independence-stronger-than-single-failure, quantitative-comparison-reveals-why-standard-is-standard; S2-E005 meta — bernstein-lp-poison-pill-3d, check-bypass-not-just-improve-bottleneck; S2-E002 meta — distinguish-constant-from-scaling-slack; S2-E004 meta — extract-precise-obstruction-from-failed-route, numerical-spectral-dns-diagnostic; S2-E003 meta — model-pde-comparison-for-mechanism-identification, test-improvability-before-pursuing-variations; S2-E001 meta — decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier, require-sensitivity-table-for-proof-analysis; E010 meta — test-generalization-before-concluding; E009 meta — adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure, adversarial-check-between-phases timing refinement; E007 meta — include-trivial-control-checks, one-task-per-exploration; E008 meta — ask-what-replaces-the-bottleneck; E006 meta — flag-cross-framework-connections.)

